	   <tr><td colspan=2>A while back I heard second-hand about a 'save buffer' in EQ : the save that's logged to the server is the 2nd or 3rd back from the latest one (why they'd do this, I do not know - why even call the most recent a 'save' then?).  Ever since then, if something happens that's really important, I make sure I get a few saves in afterwards (ok, I do this rarely, but you can try it anywhoo).  Just give someone some copper, buy something from a vendor, whatever you can find to force a save.  It's probably not worth your time (how often do the servers crash?), but if it'll amuse you at least, go ahead.  Happy Bashing!  =)   - P<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
