	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.33]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I just finished this today. I was able to do it solo at 52. (204 wis though) <br><br>I handed in the harness of control to the broodmother. As soon as I did this, invis droped, and I got attacked by the wurms near her. This is no big deal, I just ran to the giant fort. You will outrun the wurms and they will not follow that far.  I got to the fort and sat on the left side (as you look at it) invis. A few min later (enought time for me to cast chloro and med) Broodmama showed up. Targeted FF and pulled with Starfire. Got him to follow UNSNARED past the zone to EW, following tight to the wall. On the far side of the zone path,snared, doted, immolated, ro, root and med'ed. Was down to 2m at this point. From here on out I root/dot'ed. I am not sure if I pulled him far enough away or what, but Broodmother never came to his side. I had to re-snare only once.  Best advice, pull very far from fort, then snare. Root dot if you are doing this solo. And take your time. You can't do this if you get adds, and if you zone, he WILL REPOP.<br><br>*UPDATE* I have done this quest about more times, helping guildmates and such. So far, sticking to this method, I have not seen a single death, or broodmother pet. Having ES Vamps helps alot since it is a mana free dot. FF has a ton of HP, but if you are patient, and stay close to the walls, you should have no problems at all.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
