<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98968666331277></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98968666331277><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=?item=4442&mid=98968666331277>The complete lowdown...</a> <a id=fs8 href=?item=4442&mid=98968666331277#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=20 width=20></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, May 12th 12:57 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>This is an outline of the quest as I did it on the 12/05/01<br><br>Firstly, you do not need to hail or use keyphrases with any NPCs. I handed all items in whilst invis (and thus indifferent, my normal Coldain faction is dubious). There are 3 basic steps:<br><br>1) Get the sceptre from the Queen in CC. When I went in, a group had just killed her and, since nobody needed the sceptre (which I believe drops every time) they allowed me to loot. Return this to the named NPC given in the quest outline (he's located in a building on the left as you head past the guardhouse towards the hall where the Historian's giving his lecture).<br><br>2) Leave Thurgadin and head left from the river to the drakkel wolf area. I can confirm that the other wolves are placeholders for the blood wolf. Again, I got lucky as a bard was kiting the wolf and, not needing the drop, let me loot. Then, hand this and the gem to Vores, who is in a shelter by the river on the far side of the wurm caves from Thurgadin. You'll recieve a harness of control.<br><br>3) The final step is to hand this harness to the broodmother. She's on what I can only guess to be around a 24 hour spawn, and yet again I got lucky, logging in the following day to see her on track. She sets off on a trek up to the fort, and the 2 giants repop outside the fort. When she attacks, the one with the leggings runs and you should attack him once he's a resonable distance from the fort yet before he reaches the EW zone.<br><br>Now this is where I was surprised. I'm only a level 51 druid, and had a 58 druid for backup, but I could easily have killed him solo. I can only assume he's been changed since the last patch because the epic struggle outlined by another guy below was nothing like what I faced. Snare stuck on the second attempt, and my roots had about a 50 percent success rate, holding him long enough for the ES vambraces to do their work. I even had enough mana to throw a few starfires a him. He does have quite a few hps, but caused me no trouble at all.<br><br>I have no idea what happened to the broodmother, once the giant was dead I looted the leggings and left. Considering the stats, this is a remarkably easy quest, and well worth doing. When equipped, I can confirm they look like Tizmak. I just hope everyone else doing this quest is as lucky as I was )<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
