	   <tr><td colspan=2>There is, apparently, some "common knowledge" I wasn't aware of before today that I hope I can help a few of you out with.  When the Broodmother is killing Gralk and you are tracking or closing down on Fergul, HIT HIM AS SOON AS IT IS SAFE -- meaning: let him run far enough away from the Broodmother that she doesn't become his pet, but DON'T LET HIM GET TOO FAR.  What happened to me today is that the Broodmother killed Gralk before I was able to engage Fergul, and he despawned.  Had him on tracking and just got him targeted when he disappeared.  Suggestion: have a good friend waiting near the fort to help you so you don't end up wasting a lot of time on this quest.<br>&nbsp;<br>As you wander in life, whatever be your goal; keep your eye upon the doughnut, and not upon the hole</td></tr>
