	   <tr><td colspan=2>I soloed Fergul outside of the quest as a level 49 troll shaman w/o difficulty.  I invised and went inside the giant fort and rooted the other named giant then rooted and dotted Fergul.  Things got messy and I had to run but once I got close to the zone, I turned around and only Fergul was in tow so I stopped and decided to finish him.  I used nearly all my mana w/ wis of 165 but once he was out of the fort he fell pretty easily.  I am not sure if perhaps he is more difficult if you fight him while  doing the quest or not but I certainly didn't need a whole group.  BTW, he doesn't drop anything unless you follow the entire quest.  I am still waiting to catch broodmother to try to solo this quest.<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
